covered: Valid Request: Multiple success scenarios verify 200 responses with correct JSON arrays and audit levels (TC01–TC05, TC19–TC21).
Empty Response: Verified for no data and offset beyond range (TC06, TC07).
Pagination: Covered defaults, explicit offset/limit, boundaries, and large datasets including performance checks (TC01, TC02, TC05, TC07, TC16–TC18, TC21).
Query Parameters: Extensive coverage of valid and invalid parameters, including audit enum, negatives, excessive values, unexpected params, and injection attempts (TC03, TC04, TC08–TC11, TC14–TC16).
Server Errors/Resilience: Dependency failure (503) and timeout (504/appropriate) are tested (TC13, TC22).
gaps: Rate Limiting: No scenarios validating throttling behavior or 429 responses under burst traffic.
Caching Behavior: No validation of ETag/If-None-Match, Last-Modified/If-Modified-Since, or Cache-Control headers and 304 responses.
Authorization Depth: No 403 Forbidden scenario for authenticated users lacking permissions.
Response Headers: No explicit check for Content-Type=application/json as specified by Produces.
recommendations: Add rate limiting tests: send rapid successive requests to trigger throttling; expect 429 with Retry-After header; verify normal behavior when under limits.
Add caching tests: verify ETag/Cache-Control on first 200 response; re-send with If-None-Match to expect 304 Not Modified; optionally validate Last-Modified/If-Modified-Since.
Add authorization test for 403: authenticated user without required permissions should receive 403.
Add header assertions in success tests to validate Content-Type=application/json and any cache-related headers when applicable.
